				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$N.L.=\frac{paire{d}_{max}\left(\frac{NDV{I}_{x}}{AE{T}_{x}}\right)-paire{d}_{max}\left(\frac{NDV{I}_{min}}{AE{T}_{min}}\right)}{paire{d}_{max}\left(\frac{NDV{I}_{max}}{AE{T}_{max}}\right)-paire{d}_{max}\left(\frac{NDV{I}_{min}}{AE{T}_{min}}\right)}$$\end{document}where the pairedmax is for the quotient; the x subscript is for the given pixel; and the min and max are for across the entire data set to apply consistent global normalization.

